ou will know exactly why you want a DSLR."), mdx("p", null, "The take home message is: don\u2019t over-stretch yourself. Just because your compact sucks doens\u2019t mean you need a DSLR. There are a tonne of cameras in between. If your decision process lands you at an entry-level DSLR, your decision making process has probably gone wrong somewhere. The most likely scenario is that you buy an entry-level DSLR (because the others are too expensive) and once you get around to learning how to use it, and more generally about photography, you will find out the genre of photography you enjoy and want to pursue requires a bigger sensor, or higher fps, or 9 steps of exposure compensation for HDR \u2026and you need to upgrade."), mdx("p", null, "There are very few reasons to get an entry-level DSLR given the quality of EVIL/mirrorless cameras coming out these days."), mdx("h2", null, "//Do I need a new camera?"), mdx("p", null, "Probably not."), mdx("p", null, "As I said at the beginning of this post, learning to use your current camera and some post-production techniques can take you miles. You\u2019d be surprised. Learning about contrast and how the curves tool works alone will open up a whole new world of imaging to you."), mdx("p", null, "A smartphone with a good camera and a quality suite of apps will take you very far! You will be amazed at what can be achieved with such simple tools. I am a strong proponent of learning to photograph via the use of a good smartphone."), mdx("p", null, "Take a look at what ", mdx("a", {
